President Trump and Chancellor Merkel met at the International Exhibition Center in Osaka, Japan. They expressed their friendship and discussed various topics including trade, German investment in the United States, international issues, counterterrorism, and Iran. President Trump also commented on healthcare for illegal immigrants and the ongoing Democratic debates, expressing his interest in spending time with Chancellor Merkel rather than watching the debate. When asked about Germany's defense commitments, President Trump praised Chancellor Merkel as a great friend.